OL,3,CAlmost two thirds of charities axe
OL,4,Cjobs and services over financial strain
OL,6,FThe survey of 100 charity bosses also
OL,7,Ffound that 64% have already had to
OL,8,Fmake redundancies and cut vital
OL,9,Fservices because of the financial
OL,10,Fstrain.
OL,12,FAndy Pitt, head of charities at
OL,13,FRathbones, said: "Our research shows
OL,14,Fthat charities are being forced into
OL,15,Ftaking drastic measures such as
OL,16,Fhalting stock market investments,
OL,17,Fselling assets and making redundancies
OL,18,Fin order to keep afloat amid
OL,19,Fplummeting income.
