OL,3,CAlmost two thirds of charities axe
OL,4,Cjobs and services over financial strain
OL,6,F"These are impossibly difficult
OL,7,Fdecisions to make and many think it
OL,8,Fwill be a year or two until they can
OL,9,Fexpect their income to increase again."
OL,11,FThe research found that charities have
OL,12,Fbeen hit by a "perfect storm" of
OL,13,Fweaker income caused by falling
OL,14,Fdonations alongside intensifying
OL,15,Fpressure on charity staff.
OL,17,FAlmost half of charities said their
OL,18,Fincome has fallen between 10% and 15%
OL,19,Fover the past two years.
